abstract.gco:CharacterString:
The Geographic Names Ontario (Geonames) data set contains names and locations of geographic features and unincorporated places that have been officially named in Ontario, for identification and labelling purposes. It includes additional geographical referencing information:
type of feature or place location coordinates geographic township municipal and map references
And some background information behind some official names:
name status naming date name origin naming history
This layer used to be distributed under the name "Geographic Name Extent" but was modified to "Geographic Named Extent" in November 2011. See About Geographic Names for more information about the geographic names program and how to propose names for unnamed features.
Additional Documentation
Geographic Names Ontario - Data Description (PDF) Geographic Names Ontario - Documentation (Word)
Status On going: data is being continually updated
Maintenance and Update Frequency
Continual: data is repeatedly and frequently updated
Contact Geographic Names, geographicnames@ontario.ca or phone 705-761-6859

purpose.gco:CharacterString: Locations of geographic features and unincorporated places that have been officially named, or are being considered for official naming.

useLimitation.gco:CharacterString: Extents listed as unverified have not been checked for accuracy. Referencing information about most names such as the geographic township reference, lower and upper tier references and location narrative have not been checked for accuracy. Only official names (coded as A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6, A7, A8, A11, A12, A13) and official alternate names (coded as Q1) are recommended for use in most applications including general mapping. French-text Equivalent names (coded as Q2) are generally recommended for use in French text applications only.
